<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA73">
<l>iṭamvala mēḻpūṇṭa viravittē rōṭṭi</l>
<l>vaṭamuka vēṅkaṭattu maṉṉuṅ – kuṭanayanta</l>
<l>kūttaṉāy niṉṟāṉ kuraikaḻalē kūṟuvatē</l>
<l>nāttaṉṉā luḷḷa nalam</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Speaking of the tinkling anklets of him who stood as a dancer</l>
<l>who longs for pots<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For the dance with the pots see also Po. 54 (with note) and Pū. 98.</note>, who dwells on north-facing Vēṅkaṭam,</l>
<l>driving the sun chariot<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">There does not seem to be an obvious explanation at hand why and when Viṣṇu would drive the sun chariot.</note>, yoked with seven [horses] left [and] right,</l>
<l>is a good [action] that exists by the tongue itself.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
